What can you say about the numbers? Is there anything in particular that you have noticed?
Let’s look at the numbers closely.
4 8 16 32 64
From the numbers, we can say that the second number is twice the first number. This means that 4 × 2 = 8.

data.name: label1.Text
data.value: Sharon is raising chickens as a source of additional income. Among the chickens that she was raising, she chose to observe several of them as possible egg layers. She was very happy when they started laying their eggs. Sharon knew that day after day, these hens would be laying more and more eggs. She made a tally of the number of eggs her hens laid each day. The table below shows her tally.

data.name: label4.Text
data.value:
Can you still remember what an arithmetic sequence is? Well, an arithmetic sequence is a set of numbers wherein the difference between any two consecutive numbers or terms is constant (common difference).
In this lesson, you will learn about another type of number sequence—the geometric sequence. If you understood what an arithmetic sequence is, I’m sure it will also be easy for you to understand what a geometric sequence is.
Are you ready now?
